# Coding Standard (index.html / assets/js / scripts/)

Full detail: `.playbook/04_CODING_STANDARD.md`, `.playbook/10_COMPONENT_LIBRARY.md`.

- Vanilla JS + Tailwind CSS only. No build step, no framework, no new external dependency without a decision
  record in `.playbook/12_DECISIONS.md`.
- All render functions live as methods on the single `Render` namespace in `assets/js/render.js` — never as bare
  top-level `function` declarations in `index.html`.
- Every interpolated text/attribute value must go through `Render.escapeHtml()` first, except a chapter's `body`
  field, which is intentionally raw HTML and must never be escaped.
- Render functions are pure: read their arguments, return markup, never `fetch()` and never reach into outer-scope
  state directly if the data could instead be passed as a parameter.
- Whenever `Render`'s methods change, run `node scripts/verify-render.js` (it `require()`s `assets/js/render.js`
  directly — see `.playbook/17_TESTING_GUIDE.md`).
- No content hardcoded in HTML or JS — all content lives in `data/*.json`, fetched at load. Adding new content
  means editing a `data/*.json` file, not `index.html` or `render.js`.
